-- BayernLB says rejects Formula One boss Ecclestone's settlement offer
-- By Andreas Kroener
-- Fri Aug 08, 2014 11:06AM EDT
-- None



BERLIN, Aug 8 (Reuters) - German bank BayernLB [BAYLB.UL] said on Friday it had rejected a 25 million euro settlement offer by Bernie Ecclestone relating to the bank's claims the Formula One boss collected commissions and undervalued its stake in the motor racing business.

"BayernLB has rejected Mr Ecclestone's settlement offer," a spokesman for the public-sector lender told Reuters.